title: Panther Scouts #1 (2013) (digital)
description:
Panther Scouts is the oldest and largest cat youth civic organization in the world, where kittens and young cats learn the skills they need to be the cat leaders of tomorrow. The three cats of Pack 61 have a terrific opportunity in front of them when a new cat joins their school Ã¢â‚¬â€ but only one of them can get the recruitment badge. (Story and art by Aaron Veenstra & Emily Kircher.)

This is the first issue of a new, ongoing digital comic series -- #2 is scheduled for early November, with a six-week release schedule. This low-res version is available here and via the web site, pantherscouts.com. High-res versions are available at the iTunes store and Etsy, and will soon be available at Comixology. If you like it, please share and follow us on Facebook and Twitter to get updates about the next issue. And if you're in or around St. Louis, we'll be at PROJECT: Comic Con this weekend to network and get the word out.

We hope you enjoy it!
